10452"},"displayName":"Yonik Seeley","active":true},"created":"2007-08-02T17:54:36.263+0000","updated":"2007-08-02T17:54:36.263+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12375243/comment/12528942","id":"12528942","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hossman","name":"hossman","emailAddress":"hossman_apachejira at fucit dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247"},"displayName":"Hoss Man","active":true},"body":"\r\nEither LongField and DoubleField should log a warning that they not suitable for sorting (and this should be added to the javadocs) and that they defer to int/float based sorting which may have casting/parsing issues ... in which case people using small enough values will be fine.\r\n\r\n...OR...\r\n\r\nLongField and DoubleField should throw big exceptions if you try to use them to sort saying that if you wnat to Sort, use SortableLongField/SortableDoubleField\r\n\r\n(the names seem pretty intuitive to me)","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hossman","name":"hossman","emailAddress":"hossman_apachejira at fucit dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247"},"displayName":"Hoss Man","active":true},"created":"2007-09-19T22:38: